
AIM: Implement Nested Query


1. Create table student (SID, SNAME, ADDRESS, DEPT_ID) set SID primary key,
   DEPT_ID foreign key
2. Create table department (DNO, DNAME) set DNO as primary key
3. Insert values into student, dept table
4. Write a nested query to select student name and address where dept in CS
5. Write a co-related query to select student name & dept name
6. Display the number of students in each department with department name
7. Display the numbers of students in each department where no. of students < 2


QUERIES:

CREATE TABLE STUDENT (
SID NUMBER PRIMARY KEY,
SNAME VARCHAR(25),
ADDR VARCHAR(25),
DEPT_ID NUMBER FOREIGN KEY (DEPT_ID) 
REFERENCES DEPARTMENT(DEPT_ID)
);

CREATE TABLE DEPARTMENT (
DEPT_ID NUMBER PRIMARY KEY,
DEPT_NAME VARCHAR(20)
);

